window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>In the second book of John Christopher's classic series, Will Parker and his cohorts have spent a year living among the free men in the White Mountains. The Resistance charges them, now wearing realistic yet harmless caps, to infiltrate a Tripod city by competing in a sporting exhibition called \"the Games\" (very similar in nature to the Summer Olympics), in which the winners of the events are to be offered to the Tripods for service.</p>"; 
